<section class="content-center">
  <div class="content-right">
    <h3 class="item-left">Our Main Features</h3>
    <div class="item-left">
      <h4>Digital Hugs</h4>
      <p>Our primary feature. In order to chat with another user, a hug must be sent. A hug is like any regular text message, however all initial hugs are sent in response to a randomly selected prompt. Furthermore, hugs have a 20 word minimum, ensuring that messages sent have enough content to spark a decent conversation. Once a hug is sent, the receiving user can opt to either accept or reject the hug. When the user accepts a hug they are required to send a message back (without the prompt or word minimum requirement of the initial hug message). When a hug is accepted and sent back, users are then able to freely message each other like in any other messaging platform. If a hug is rejected, the receiver does not send a hug back, although the sender is not notified of the rejection.</p>
    </div>
    <img class="item-right medium" src="/assets/images/fouro/fouro-icon-hug.png"/>
  </div>
  <div class="content-right">
    <div class="item-left">
      <h4>Keep In Touch Friends List</h4>
      <p>In order to encourage users to reach out to different people and maintain a healthy and diverse social circle, the friends list is not ordered by most recent interactions, rather the opposite. Friends you have not reached out to for a while will be displayed at the top of the friends list, and friends you have just messaged will be at the bottom of your friends list. This provides users the opportunity to easily access and contact friends that they have not spoken to in a while.</p>
    </div>
    <img class="item-right medium" src="/assets/images/fouro/fouro-icon-friends.png"/>
  </div>
  <div class="content-right">
    <div class="item-left">
      <h4>Four Hugs A Day Streak</h4>
      <p>Through our user research we found that users are most motivated to send messages to each other when they have some sort of incentive/track record to protect. Much like snapchat streaks, we implemented our own streak feature that keeps track of how many hugs a user has sent in a single day, as well as the number of days the user has sent and received 4 or more hugs (again keeping in line with the 4 hugs a day idea).</p>
    </div>
    <img class="item-right medium" src="/assets/images/fouro/fouro-icon-streaks.png"/>
  </div>
</section>
